🎬 CASTING: CHARACTERFUL BOYS — CAPE TOWN 🎬

We’re looking for a confident, characterful boy for a TV commercial shooting in Cape Town at the end of January 2026.

Who we’re scouting:
• Confident boy around 10 years old (may be slightly younger or older)
• Stocky build
• Caucasian
• Big personality
• Loves to dance, move, and express himself

This role is all about confidence, charm, and natural energy 💃🕺

📩 If your child fits this brief (or you know someone who does), please email us with details, recent photos, and any dance or movement clips if available:

👉 studio@zestcasting.com

⏰ Deadline: 13 January 2026 @ 10:00

items.text:
“We’re Hiring!!  

CAPE TOWN ONLY PLEASE!

We are seeking a dynamic, charismatic, and articulate Game Show Host to lead our live and recorded show in Africa’s first ever live studio!  
The ideal candidate will bring energy, professionalism, and charm to every broadcast, engaging audiences while maintaining the integrity and excitement of the show.  

This is a front-facing role that requires confidence on camera, quick thinking, a sense of humour and an ability to connect naturally with diverse audiences.  

SO LADIES (aged 18-35 and also between 167cm & 175m tall) please get in touch for more details!  

How to Apply: Please submit your CV, headshot, and demo reel or showreel (if available) to  recruit@ppgafrica.com

🔥 Pegas Touristic срочно ищет ОДНОГО универсального парня-танцора НА ЗАМЕНУ

для работы в танцевальных шоу сети отелей Swandor во Вьетнаме 🇻🇳

📅 Сезон 2026

🕒 Старт контракта: 1 февраля 2026

📆 Длительность: от 12 месяцев (минимум)

⸻

❇️ ТРЕБОВАНИЯ:

🕺 Рост от 175 см

👯‍♂️ Возраст от 21 лет

🪩 Классическая / народная / бальная база

🤝 Опыт работы в поддержках с партнёршей

🗣 Только русскоговорящие артисты

⸻

📝 КОМПАНИЯ ПРЕДОСТАВЛЯЕТ:

✅ Авиаперелёт туда-обратно

✅ Рабочую визу

✅ Медицинскую страховку

✅ Проживание (по 2 человека в номерах отеля)

✅ 3-разовое питание «шведский стол»

✅ Полностью оплачиваемый репетиционный период

⸻

✔️ 1 вечернее шоу в день (40–45 минут)

✔️ 1–2 репетиции в день

⸻

❗️ По всем вопросам и за дополнительной информацией — в ЛС ❗️

items.text:
Hey-Yah All ! Ein gesundes neues Jahr an alle.

Wir haben schon in einigen Filmen mitgespielt, auch in Serien.

Mein Mann hatte eine Rolle in "Unser Letzter Sommer" von Michal Rogalski. 

In Frankreich war er für den offiziellen D´Artagnan Verein der berühmte Musketier und hatte auch in der Fechtszene einen Namen.

Für die Szenen, Ausrüstung, zeitgnössische Fechtkleidung, Szenenbild, Training der Fechter, sowie das Fechten selbst im damaligen Stil zeichnete sich mein Mann im Film "Race" (Zeit für Legenden) aus: Roland Sonntag @ IMDB.

Wir schreiben und performen aktuell den guten alten Rock´n Roll auf unsere eigene neue Art und Weise.

Das Bild entstand auf der RBB Bühne Antenne Brandenburg der Berliner Woche letztes Jahr, woe wir das MKC -  Multikulturelles Centrum Templin e.V. offiziell vertraten. Die gesamte Meesehalle tanzte, sang und feierte.

Wir stehen gerne weiterhin für Film, TV, Werbung und besonders gerne auch für einen Genre-Film zur Verfügung. Uns gibt es immer nur im Doppelpack, weswegen wir z.B. schon 2 Anfragen für eine Kultserie abgesagt hatten. Man wollte nur Brigitte mit dem Kontrabass. Sorry. Wir sind unzertrennlich.

Natürlich lassen wir uns auch sehr gerne für Konzerte und Festivals buchen.

Außer ein paar kleinen privaten Youtube Filmchen und unseren Facebook Account machten wir bisher keine Werbung. 

Viele liebe Grüße an alle, auch an die die wir nicht kennen, Euer Ronny Guittar Duo mit Brigitte Bass Vom Duo

items.text:
STOP WAITING. START ACTING. 🎬

If you’re an actor… you need to be constantly acting.

Not “thinking about acting.”
Not “planning to act next year.”
Not waiting for someone to pick you.

Because the actors who win?
They don’t wait for permission.

They stay in the game every week.

✅ Train consistently (classes aren’t optional — they’re maintenance)
✅ Get work (yes, the small jobs matter too)
✅ Create work (short films, monologues, scenes, content)
✅ Volunteer for formal shorts/student films and build real credits
✅ Stay sharp with peripheral acting jobs:

🎭 Role play / corporate training
🎙 Voiceover
🩺 Medical role play (nurse/patient scenarios)
🕵️ Mystery events
📣 Promo & immersive experiences

Some actors look down on this stuff…

But the real pros know.

👇 Join the movement here:
linktr.ee/mattzina

message.text:
STOP WAITING. START ACTING. 🎬

If you’re an actor… you need to be constantly acting.

Not “thinking about acting.”
Not “planning to act next year.”
Not waiting for someone to pick you.

Because the actors who win?
They don’t wait for permission.

They stay in the game every week.

✅ Train consistently (classes aren’t optional — they’re maintenance)
✅ Get work (yes, the small jobs matter too)
✅ Create work (short films, monologues, scenes, content)
✅ Volunteer for formal shorts/student films and build real credits
✅ Stay sharp with peripheral acting jobs:

🎭 Role play / corporate training
🎙 Voiceover
🩺 Medical role play (nurse/patient scenarios)
🕵️ Mystery events
📣 Promo & immersive experiences

Some actors look down on this stuff…

But the real pros know.

👇 Join the movement here:
linktr.ee/mattzina

items.text:
**044  Mini serial  wojenny 1940 – Kobieta w stylu lat 30 -  stych  (casting on-line )**

 

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonatów **‘’Grupa1940’’** poszukuje  kobiety w wieku 20 – 30 do sesji fotograficznej w stylu lat 30 stych. Jedno zdjęcie będzie wykorzystane na obrazie ,które z kolei zostanie powieszone w biurze niemieckiego majora SS.

 

Szukamy osoby bez permanentnych brwi czy farbowanych włosów, bez kolczyków na twarzy. Mile widziana osoba z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrza czy Katowic.

** **

**Na wiosnę roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjęc do tego **projektu. Będziemy realizować mini serial oparty o wątki grupy okultystycznej ’’**Ahnenerbe’**’ która chce zdobyć słynne artefakty ale w tym ktoś im chce przeszkadzać. Projekt będzie  się składać z 6 odcinków po 10/12 minut każdy. Będziemy też sukcesywnie dodawać inne ogłoszenia związane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjęcia aktualne. Na zdjęciu powyżej osoba będzie mieć podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materiały są z naszej sesji.** Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Od 01.04.25 założyliśmy swój kanał na portalu youtube z filmami z naszych planów żeby można było zobaczyć jak to u nas wygląda od kuchni. 

 

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE8KyfwpyFGzzwUDqdwy74g

 

 

.** Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

**Serial nie jest stworzony z sympatii do tej nazistowskiej organizacji lecz wynika to z samego scenariusza aby ukazał zbrodnie i sam fakt iż była w pełni zła. W produkcji znajdą się osoby, które będą chcieć walczyć i potępiać te wielkie zło jakim był nazizm. W oparciu o Dz.U.2017.0.2204 t.j. - Ustawa z dnia 6 czerwca 1997 r. - Kodeks karny,Art. 256 "Propagowanie faszyzmu lub innego ustroju totalitarnego lub nawoływanie domnienawiści", §3 - nie narusza prawa proponując przedmiot do celów historycznych lub kolekcjonerskich.**

# **POSZUKUJEMY AKTORÓW DO FILMU DYPLOMOWEGO (THRILLER Z CZARNYM HUMOREM)** 

**Role:**
* **Ojciec** (mężczyzna **45–65**)
* **Mati** (mężczyzna **20–30**)
* **Kondziu** (mężczyzna **20–30**)
##  **Kraków**
 **25 stycznia**
Projekt **non-profit** (zwrot kosztów dojazdu + jedzenie na planie)

Zgłoszenia **na priv / w komentarzu**: imię, wiek, 1–2 zdjęcia + link do showreela/IG.

❗️Dringend❗️
Casting-Aufruf – Schauspieler gesucht, 18–20 Jahre im Raum Stuttgart (Umgebung)

Logline: Ein unsicherer Lehrer, der vergeblich um Respekt kämpft, wird durch den Spott seiner Schüler so radikal verändert, dass er vom Gutmütigen zum gnadenlosen Strengen mutiert. 

Für einen Diploma-Kurzfilm (ca. 6–7 Minuten) im Genre Komödie suche ich sehr kurzfristig einen männlichen 

Schauspieler im Spielalter 18–20 Jahre für eine Nebenrolle mit Text. Drehtage sind am 14.01.26 und 15.01.26.

Die Rolle ist die eines Schülers. Der Textumfang ist überschaubar und umfasst ca. vier Sätze.

Leider hat die ursprünglich zugesagte Besetzung unerwartet kurzfristig abgesagt, weshalb ich nun zeitnah einen passenden Darsteller suche.

Rahmenbedingungen:

• Low-Budget-Produktion (Diplomfilm)

• Vergütung im Low-Budget-Bereich

• Fahrtkosten werden erstattet

Ich freue mich über schnelle Rückmeldungen und kurze Bewerbungen (gern mit Foto/Showreel, falls vorhanden).

Bewerbung bitte per E-Mail!

Kontakt: Bianca Brandner 

                brandner.bianca@web.de

items.text:
Darsteller für atmosphärischen Filmtrailer gesucht!

Hallo an alle! Für einen Proof-of-Concept (POC)
Trailer mit intensiver spanischer Stimmung suche ich einen ausdrucksstarken Mann, der Lust hat, ein besonderes Projekt mit zum Leben zu erwecken.

Wen ich suche:
• Du hast einen südeuropäischen / mediterranen Look.
• Du kannst dich sehr gut bewegen zu Latin Musik und hast ein gutes Körpergefühl.          •hast Lust auf ein kreatives Projekt mit viel Leidenschaft und Rhythmus.
Zum Projekt:

Wir drehen einen Tanz-PoC , den wir bei internationalen Festivals einreichen werden. Das Ziel ist es, aus diesem POC ein großeres Filmprojekt zu entwickeln. Das ist eine super Chance für deine Sichtbarkeit.

Da es ein No-Budget-Herzensprojekt ist, gibt es keine Gage, aber:
Wir übernehmen deine Reisekosten.
Es gibt volle Verpflegung am Set.
Sichtbarkeit bei Festivals.

Hast du Lust auf spanische Vibes und eine tolle Zusammenarbeit? Dann schreib mir gerne eine Nachricht mit Foto oder einem kurzen Video über mediterran-film@web.de .

Ich freue mich auf dich !

Hello everyone,

 

Join the one and only Mark Winstanley for a 4-week online course: Playing with Life's Gestures

 

Mark is an inspirational teacher who has taught at some of the most prestigious theatre and acting schools in the world, including the École Philippe Gaulier, the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art (RADA), and East 15 Acting School.

** **

*"A playful provocateur, he guides his students towards discovering their unique sense of pleasure, presence, and freedom in performance"*

 

Over the four weeks you will study the language of gesture and movement as a pathway to creative freedom.

 

Every Tuesday between the 3rd of February and the 24th of February on Zoom between 7pm and 9pm (UK time).

 

This workshop is open to anyone wanting to dig further into their acting practice.

 

Pay what you can, we suggest £80 for the whole course.

 

Email us to register your interest on theperformersplayground@gmail.com or book here: https://www.theperformersplayground.com/online-course

Through playful physical exercises and text work, you'll learn to uncover the impulse beneath the words finding authenticity, spontaneity, and connection in your performance. February 3rd until February 24th Online Pay what you can, we suggest 오80 for the whole course THEPERFORMERSPLAYGROUND.CO.UK'

items.text:
An actor was just asking how to start. I thought I'd post the answer I gave him here. 

Just in case anyone else has the same question.  

Classes are the place to start. 

Once you get into classes you'll meet people who can help you but here are a few things you can do right away. 

1. Think of your self as a professional right away. Get a schedule together for your practice time. 

Read scripts. 

Think of the movies you like and google them plus screenplay, you should find them. 

Professionals read full scripts so start doing that. 

2. Have a look at yourself in the mirror and think about which actors you share a look with. Many actors want to be cast in an action hero role when they look like the sidekick. 

If that's the case (not saying it is - just an example) you need to live like an action hero actor. That means the food and workout routines and practicing those kinds of scenes. 

3. Learn the craft. Get really good at both acting and auditioning. They are 2 separate beasts. 

You know when you see a shitty actor on screen and you think, "I would be so much better." 

They're probably great at auditioning. So learn them both.

Hope this helps. 

We have a free class every Tuesday at 12:30 pm pacific. Message me for the link if you'd like to join us.

items.summary:
An actor was just asking how to start. I thought I'd post the answer I gave him here. 

Just in case anyone else has the same question.  

Classes are the place to start. 

Once you get into classes you'll meet people who can help you but here are a few things you can do right away. 

1. Think of your self as a professional right away. Get a schedule together for your practice time. 

Read scripts. 

Think of the movies you like and google them plus screenplay, you should find them. 

Professionals read full scripts so start doing that. 

2. Have a look at yourself in the mirror and think about which actors you share a look with. Many actors want to be cast in an action hero role when they look like the sidekick. 

If that's the case (not saying it is - just an example) you need to live like an action hero actor. That means the food and workout routines and practicing those kinds of scenes. 

3. Learn the craft. Get really good at both acting and auditioning. They are 2 separate beasts. 

You know when you see a shitty actor on screen and you think, "I would be so much better." 

They're probably great at auditioning. So learn them both.

Hope this helps. 

We have a free class every Tuesday at 12:30 pm pacific. Message me for the link if you'd like to join us.

**Casting Call - 1970s Biographical Feature Film**

For a new biographical feature film set in the 1970s, we are looking for **MEN aged approx. 20-35, up to 180 cm max., **an athletic build. In role** future MILITARY PERSONNEL**.

Gentlemen of the following origins are particularly welcome:
* **CUBANS**
* **MONGOLIANS**
* **BULGARIANS**
* **HULGARIANS**

**Shooting Days:**
* February 5 – shooting in Warsaw
* March 18 – shooting in Warsaw
* March 26 – shooting in Piła (transport and hotel provided)
* May 1 – shooting likely in Warsaw (TBC)

**Rate: 450 PLN per shooting day**

**Characterization Guidelines:**
* Absolutely no tattoos
* Hair must be short, but cut without the use of clippers
* No facial hair (clean-shaven)
* Athletic build

**Please send applications to:** **ewelina.wika@podtytulem.pl**
**Subject Line:** **KKZ**
**Email Content:** Name and surname, age, phone number, city/town of residence, nationality + measurements: height, chest, waist, hips, clothing and shoe size.
**Attachment:** **PHOTO OF FACE AND FIGURE: taken only on the day of application + profile photo**

**FACE PHOTO** – portrait selfie in daylight, straight-on, looking into the lens. No filters. No glasses. No head covering.
**FIGURE PHOTO** – in clothing that shows the outline of the figure.

Hi, I’m Kae Tapscott, I’m 18 and FTM. I’ve been acting since the age of six and have extensive experience in both musical theatre and straight plays. My stage credits include pantomimes and musicals such as Snow White, Cinderella, Mary Poppins: The Musical, Aladdin, Beauty and the Beast, A Christmas Carol, The Grinch, Bugsy Malone, The Addams Family: The Musical, and We Will Rock You. I’ve also appeared in plays including Burning Monkey and The Donahue Sisters. I’m currently in my second year of Acting for Stage and Screen Level 3 at Coleg Gwent, Crosskeys Campus, and recently played Dean in Pronoun. I’ve applied to the Bristol School of Acting and have a recall audition on January 24th.

Headshot and showreel below.

AUDITIONS OPEN: Collection of Short Plays in March in London

Happy New Year! We’re Broadmai Productions, and we’re excited to announce that auditions are now open for our upcoming performance, HAYWIRE: The Dark Side of New Technology. The performances will be held at The Drayton Arms on 22nd & 23rd March 2026, starting at 7:30 PM each night. (Cast required all day on 22nd March for get-in and from 18:00 each night). 

Auditions will be online and open tomorrow, 13th January, and continue until 24th January. All ages, genders and levels of experience welcome. If you’re interested in auditioning, please email us at: contact@broadmai-productions.co.uk

Please express interest by 23rd January.

Once you reach out, we’ll send you the scripts for the four short plays: PostMax6000, Wonderful, Beyond the Grave, and Simon. 

_______

AUDITION DETAILS:

 • Auditions are 20-minute slots. You will be asked to audition with 2-3 pages of your choice from the provided scripts.

 • Ideally, be off book, but it’s fine if not. 

 • The characters are flexible in terms of gender and age, except those for Beyond the Grave, which requires two male actors who resemble father and son.

_______

PLAY DESCRIPTIONS:

 • PostMax 6000: The PostMax 6000 is invented! A vast underground postal system capable of delivering

hundreds of letters across the country per second! But what’s this?! It’s just sucked Kinkelbert George inside! Will he be delivered to freedom? Or lost in postal purgatory?

 • Wonderful: Ben signs up for a research programme for a new-age medical device. It can detect hereditary

illness and diseases that he could develop…but it also lets him know, and hear, exactly how his

ancestors died. As detections become increasingly intense, Ben learns that knowledge about death is better left untold — especially when it comes to children.

 • Beyond the Grave: A mysterious phone is delivered. When it rings, Reece answers it and finds his deceased father on the other end. Overwhelmed to hear his voice again and to learn that there is a way to bring him back to life, Reece starts to wonder if the rules of death are better left unbroken…

 • Simon: Simon has an all-inclusive getaway booked and paid for by his work. The location is perfect, the

hotel is perfect, Simon is perfect. And so is Simon — the other Simon. And the other Simon. Wait, how many Simons are there?! Who’s the real Simon?!

_______

REHEARSALS: 

 • Rehearsals will be in-person in London, with a commitment of 1-2 sessions per week until the performances.

items.summary:
AUDITIONS OPEN: Collection of Short Plays in March in London

Happy New Year! We’re Broadmai Productions, and we’re excited to announce that auditions are now open for our upcoming performance, HAYWIRE: The Dark Side of New Technology. The performances will be held at The Drayton Arms on 22nd & 23rd March 2026, starting at 7:30 PM each night. (Cast required all day on 22nd March for get-in and from 18:00 each night). 

Auditions will be online and open tomorrow, 13th January, and continue until 24th January. All ages, genders and levels of experience welcome. If you’re interested in auditioning, please email us at: contact@broadmai-productions.co.uk

Please express interest by 23rd January.

Once you reach out, we’ll send you the scripts for the four short plays: PostMax6000, Wonderful, Beyond the Grave, and Simon. 

_______

AUDITION DETAILS:

 • Auditions are 20-minute slots. You will be asked to audition with 2-3 pages of your choice from the provided scripts.

 • Ideally, be off book, but it’s fine if not. 

 • The characters are flexible in terms of gender and age, except those for Beyond the Grave, which requires two male actors who resemble father and son.

_______

PLAY DESCRIPTIONS:

 • PostMax 6000: The PostMax 6000 is invented! A vast underground postal system capable of delivering

hundreds of letters across the country per second! But what’s this?! It’s just sucked Kinkelbert George inside! Will he be delivered to freedom? Or lost in postal purgatory?

 • Wonderful: Ben signs up for a research programme for a new-age medical device. It can detect hereditary

illness and diseases that he could develop…but it also lets him know, and hear, exactly how his

ancestors died. As detections become increasingly intense, Ben learns that knowledge about death is better left untold — especially when it comes to children.

 • Beyond the Grave: A mysterious phone is delivered. When it rings, Reece answers it and finds his deceased father on the other end. Overwhelmed to hear his voice again and to learn that there is a way to bring him back to life, Reece starts to wonder if the rules of death are better left unbroken…

 • Simon: Simon has an all-inclusive getaway booked and paid for by his work. The location is perfect, the

hotel is perfect, Simon is perfect. And so is Simon — the other Simon. And the other Simon. Wait, how many Simons are there?! Who’s the real Simon?!

_______

REHEARSALS: 

 • Rehearsals will be in-person in London, with a commitment of 1-2 sessions per week until the performances.

_______

COMPENSATION:

 • This will be a profit-share arrangement, with profits distributed after expenses are covered.

items.text:
Hello everyone. 
After taking a nearly 2 year break from acting I've decided I want to get into it again but feel completely lost. I am 17 years old and have been in independent films along with stage productions. How should I go about getting back into it? 
Thank you

topComments.text: Get hold of a copy of the Actors and Performers Yearbook, which will give you a solid overview into how the UK industry functions. A library should have a copy, or could order one for you to borrow, or you might find a copy second-hand on ebay. The best way to build the foundation for a successful long-term career is to go to one of the top drama schools and train intensely for three years. There's no argument, statistically, against that. However, there are an increasing number of part-time schools, shorter courses and online training options. Most of the drama schools tend to prefer students with a little more life experience, though getting in at 18 years old can happen. In the meantime, take some classes, keep working in the theatre, keep doing student films. There are a few casting platforms you can join once you're 18: sites like Mandy, Backstage or Casting Callback. It's not too hard to pick up bits and pieces of work as an actor: character work in theme parks, unpaid films, student projects, profit-share theatre etc. However, paying the bills with acting work is another matter, and would need you to reach a very good level in terms of your skills, discipline, work ethic and ability to deal with the ups and downs of the industry.

New head shots. Show reel material. Spotlight registration then agent and then hustle hustle hustle. It’s a tough  industry at the moment but out the leg work in, do your ground work and you will do it.

Filmmakers!. Unleash your creativity and join a vibrant community of passionate filmmakers who are dedicated to bringing stories to life! Together, we'll craft captivating narrative films, forge valuable connections, and fuel our artistic visions. 

This is more than just filmmaking; it's a journey to elevate our craft and careers to new heights! Every Saturday from 4-6 PM near DTLA, we gather to share ideas, collaborate, and inspire one another. If you're truly committed to making an impact in the world of film and ready to embark on this exciting adventure, we invite you to become a part of our filmmaking family. Membership is completely free! 

Complete this form to join us. https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7

items.text:
## 🎬 CASTING CALL — JERRY

**Project:** Lie Detector (Short Film)
**Genre:** Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller
**Location:** Lower Mainland, BC
**Shoot Dates:**  Sundays Jan 25 or Sunday Feb 01
**Compensation:** Volunteer / Passion Project (Reel‑worthy material)

**Actors looking to play a layered character outside their comfort zone are strongly encouraged to apply.**

ROLE: JERRY

**Age Range:** 30–45
**Ethnicity:** Caucasian

**Gender:** Male
CHARACTER SNAPSHOT

Jerry is Amber’s husband — thoughtful, intelligent, and quietly dependable. He’s the kind of man people trust instinctively. Soft‑spoken. Observant. Safe. Which is exactly why he’s unpredictable.

Jerry isn’t loud, cruel, or obviously broken. His betrayal doesn’t come from malice, but from emotional absence — a man who learned to disappear while standing right next to someone. When the truth surfaces, it’s not explosive. It’s devastating in its calm.

This role lives in restraint. What Jerry *doesn’t* say matters more than what he does.

PERFORMANCE NOTES
* Subtle, internal performance
* Strong control of silence, pauses, and micro‑expressions
* Chemistry with Amber is critical — intimacy without sentimentality
* We’re looking for an actor who can make the audience *want to believe him*

This is **not** a villain role. It’s a human one.

WHY THIS ROLE MATTERS

Jerry sits at the emotional fault line of the story.

His choices force Amber to confront the limits of technology, trust, and perception.

Handled well, this role will linger with the audience long after the film ends.

Please apply at soultales.ca@gmail.com

Hello all,

I’m a filmmaker from Markham, Ontario directing a feature film funded by Telefelim Canada’s Talent-To-Watch program. Searching for my  TWO leads, both of Filipino background. If you think you know anyone that would be interested please share.

Info below!

CANADA-WIDE CASTING CALL (Non-Union) // AWAY WITH DAD // FEATURE FILM

Paid Opportunity
Filming Location: Renfrew County, Ontario
Tentative dates: Mid August - End of September 2026

Set in Algonquin Park, Away With Dad is a candid story of a father and his adult son who make the drastic decision of going on a backpacking trip in the wilderness with no running water or electricty in order to focus on creating a stronger bond between them.

Casting for the following Lead Roles:
Thomas - Male, Filipino, 45 - 65 years old, speaks Visayan or Tagalog
TJ - Male, Filipino, 20 - 35 years old

NO ACTING EXPERIENCE REQUIRED. Camping experience an asset. Must be a Canadian Citizen. 

Director: Kyle Credo Producer: Farah Abdo 
If interested please email office@awdfilm.com a photo of yourself and a video (2 minutes MAX) stating your full name, what languages you can speak. For the remainder of the video please tell us about yourself: your upbringing, where you grew up and your hobbies, likes, dislikes, etc. Anything that helps us get to know you better!" us get to know you better!"

FEATURED STATISTER SØGES
Vi søger featured statister M/K/NB i alderen 28-45 til en kortfilm af Agnes Trier. Castet inkluderer Filippa Coster-Waldau, Jacob Lohmann, Olivia Joof, Sidsel Siem Koch og Kitt Maiken Mortensen. 

Pitch

Emma er midt i tyverne og utilpas i rollen som nybagt mor. Til et forældremøde i vuggestuen må Emma gøre op med sig selv hvor langt hun vil gå for at skjule sine sande følelser.

Tristans mor er en karakterundersøgelse af en ung kvinde i en sårbar periode.

Praktisk info:

Du skal spille en forældre i forældregruppen, så det vigtigt du kan deltage i optagelser hele dagen d. 24/1+25/1 i tidsrummet 8-18, og meget gerne også en halv dag i aftentimerne mandag. d. 26/1.

Erfaring med improvisation og replikker er en fordel, men ikke et krav.

Jobbet er ulønnet men vi søger for forplejning og god energi. ☀️

Vi filmer i Sydhavnen.

Ved interesse send vellignende billede, samt navn, alder og erfaring til casting@adomeitfilm.com

PILOT / PROMO / FESTIVAL-KORTFILM

VIKINGEPERIODEN

Kun 5 dages optagelse + en dags opsamling.

Passionsprojekt med stjernespækket cast og crew

Prisvindende instruktør og fotograf

Optagelser:

Brøndbyskoven / Albertslund Vikingelandsby

Det bliver Uge 9–10 (februar) måske før man må lige være lidt flex!

Vi søger:

10 årig pige skandinavisk udseende langt hår rødt / lysebrunt / mørkeblond 

 • 2 Runners med gyldigt kørekort til pack up pack down og ad hoc opgaver

 • Makeup & hår – fletninger i skæg og hår og war paint 

Forplejning:

Der er frokost på settet hver dag – og enkelte dage også aftensmad.

Medbring selv drikkevarer.

Vilkår:

Sorry not sorry – det er ikke nemt at lave film uden budget.

Til gengæld får du erfaring, netværk og et stærkt projekt på CV’et.

Det bliver skide skægt og mega spændende 🔥

Kontakt:

Send mail til yummiversal@gmail.com

Emnefelt: VIKING

CASTING CALL – INDEPENDENT FEATURE FILM
Project Title: After the ashes 
Production Type: Independent Feature Film
Shoot Dates: January 23rd - 25th
Location: Denver, CO 
Compensation: $1000 + IMDb Credit 

SYNOPSIS 
Four young adults reunite in their hometown for a classmate’s memorial weekend, only to confront old wounds, hidden desires, and unresolved conflicts. Over 48 tense hours together, buried truths surface and a forbidden revelation threatens to break their fragile bond forcing each of them to face who they were and who they hope to become.

NOW CASTING – LEAD & SUPPORTING ROLES:

LEAD ROLES:
Noah (Male, 18–23)
Stoic, thoughtful, and emotionally guarded. Once the glue of the group, now struggling with guilt tied to the friend they lost.
Ava (Female, 18–24)
Warm, steady, and empathic, the peacemaker. She carries a long-hidden emotional connection to one of the group members that threatens to spill out.
Riley (Female, 19–25)
Fiery, outspoken, and fearlessly honest. She uses humor to mask deep abandonment issues and unresolved grief.

SUPPORTING ROLES:
Harper (Female, 18–23)
Soft-spoken, artistic, and intuitive. She sees what the others try to hide and becomes the catalyst for the group’s emotional reckoning.
Mr. Hayes (Male, 30s–40s)
A grounded, compassionate former mentor to the group. He carries his own guilt for not noticing their struggles sooner, and his presence forces the characters to confront their past.

TO SUBMIT:
Email your headshot, resume, and city of residence to:
filmsofacclaim@gmail.com 
Subject line:
“[Your Name] – After the ashes”

CASTING CALL FOR STUDENT FILM “NEWLYWED”
Overview: Nadia Ritter grapples with the expectations of womanhood during her first week of marriage.

Genre: Film Noir

Compensation: Unpaid

Location: Denver Park Hill Area

Characters Needed:
Nadia Ritter: Female, Early 20’s, values connection and vulnerability above all else
Roy Johnson: Male, early 20’s, conditioned by social standards of what a man has to be
Sarah Ritter: (Voice only) Nadia’s mom, late 50’s, well intentioned but comes off strongly

OTHER INFORMATION:
There will be 1-2 filming dates on a weekend during late January to early February. We can be flexible on the exact dates.

HOW TO AUDITION: 
Text 720-305-8418 or email zmchudd@gmail.com with subject “newlywed audition” and I will reply with dialogue for you to read on camera.

**Er du mellem 12 og 24 år – og har du lyst til at være med i en kampagne, der gør en forskel?**🎬

Til en ny kampagne for **Genklang** søger vi børn og unge, både drenge og piger, der har lyst til at medvirke i en kampagnevideo, som skal deles på Genklangs sociale medier og online univers.

**Om kampagnen: *****Når ferien larmer mest***

Ferier forbindes ofte med frihed og glæde.
Men for mange børn og unge kan ferier være svære – fordi skolen og fritidsaktiviteter holder lukket, og man er mere hjemme, end man har lyst til.

Med kampagnen “Når ferien larmer mest” vil vi vise små, genkendelige øjeblikke, hvor unge forsøger at trække sig, gemme sig eller finde ro. Kampagnen skal skabe genkendelse og vise, at man ikke er alene.

**Hvem er Genklang?**

Genklang er et tilbud – både fysisk og online – for børn og unge mellem 12 og 24 år, som vokser op i hjem med alkohol- eller stofproblematikker. Genklang er finansieret af Social- og Boligstyrelsen og åbnede d. 1. september. Du kan læse mere her: [https://genklang.dk/](https://genklang.dk/) 

**👉 Vi søger dig, hvis du:**
* er mellem **12 og 24 år**
* har lyst til at medvirke i en **meningsfuld kampagne**

Du behøver **ikke** have skuespilerfaring.

Optagelserne foregår i Aarhus, og vi sørger selvfølgelig for at dække transport i forbindelse med medvirken.

**📩 Interesseret eller nysgerrig?**

Skriv til os på:
**caou@carelink.dk**

Har du spørgsmål, er du meget velkommen til at kontakte os – også bare for at høre mere.

items.text:
Hallo liebe Gruppe der Schauspieler und Freunde des Films 🎬

Nach nun mehrere Jahren freue ich mich durch meine Leidenschaft und Engagement für diese Gruppe eine so tolle große Community aufbauen zu können. 

Es ist etwas her als ich die Gruppe übernommen habe mit rund 700 Mitgliedern 
Nun sind wir hoch vierstellig und ich freue mich auf ein neues Jahr mit euch. 

Ich hoffe viele von euch konnten tolle Angebote und Castings erreichen über die Gruppe. 
Viele verschiedene Projekte sind über die Jahre zustande gekommen. 

Ich selbst kann leider nicht eure Angebote wahrnehmen, jedoch hat dies persönliche und familiäre Gründe. 

Nachdem die Gruppe jedoch trotz allem viel Arbeit macht, würde ich mich sehr freuen über etwas Unterstützung. 
Zum einen gerne jemanden der als Moderator helfen möchte. 
Zum anderen wer etwas zurück geben möchte für mein Engagement damit ihr / du euer Projekt erfolgreich promoten konntet, ihr / du ein tolles Angebot gefunden habt, wo ihr viel Spaß hattet und eure Karriere voran bringen konntet. 

Ich freue mich auf jede Unterstützung und Spende für meine Projekte in Zanzibar, Tanzania 🇹🇿 

Revolut 
@marcel2p53

PayPal 
@Backpackerhelp

Wise
@marceln31

items.text:
🎥 Looking for Confident On-Camera Talent for Public Interaction TikTok Videos 

I’m looking for a confident, charismatic on-camera personality for a series of short-form, public-interaction videos for a wellness brand.

This role is heavily improv-based. You’ll be approaching people in public and engaging in real, unscripted conversations on camera. The ability to think on your feet, read people quickly, and go back-and-forth naturally is essential.

This is not scripted acting. The content is playful, high-energy, conversational, and humor-driven — not aggressive or mean-spirited.

You do not need to film or edit anything. I will handle all production. You just need to be comfortable on camera and talking to strangers.

$20/hour 

Please send any similar content you’ve done or even your Instagram/tiktok link helps.

topComments.text:
Hello! 

I would be perfect for this.

I’m a naturally charismatic and outgoing person who thrives on connecting with others. I’ve dabbled in comedy and commercial acting, which has given me strong improv skills and the confidence to think on my feet in unscripted situations. I’m also very comfortable on camera, having performed regularly as a singer on my church’s worship team, which has taught me how to engage an audience and be authentic in front of people.

I genuinely enjoy playful, high-energy interactions and have a knack for reading people quickly and responding naturally — exactly what’s needed for spontaneous public engagement content. I’m confident I can bring fun, relatable energy to your TikTok videos while making people feel at ease on camera.

I’m interested, but have no context.

When? Where? For how long? 

What will I be asked to talk about or react? 

I’m a great improviser, but won’t step in front of a camera without more security/context.

Gern kannst du den Fragebogen bereits jetzt über folgenden Link ausfüllen:

https://form.jotform.com/260054741703046

Alle eingegangenen Bewerbungen werden selbstverständlich bearbeitet. Sobald eine Entscheidung getroffen wurde oder weitere Angaben benötigt werden, melden wir uns direkt.

Vielen Dank für eure Geduld und euer Vertrauen.

Mit freundlichen Grüßen

Kiliaan Dornwald

KiliaanFilms

KiliaanFilms@outlook.de

CAPE TOWN ONLY PLEASE!

We are seeking a dynamic, charismatic, and articulate Game Show Host to lead our live and recorded show in Africa’s first ever live studio!  
The ideal candidate will bring energy, professionalism, and charm to every broadcast, engaging audiences while maintaining the integrity and excitement of the show.  

This is a front-facing role that requires confidence on camera, quick thinking, a sense of humour and an ability to connect naturally with diverse audiences.  

SO LADIES (aged 18-35 and also between 167cm & 175m tall) please get in touch for more details!

items.text:
STOP WAITING. START ACTING. 🎬

If you’re an actor… you need to be constantly acting.

Not “thinking about acting.”
Not “planning to act next year.”
Not waiting for someone to pick you.

Because the actors who win?
They don’t wait for permission.

They stay in the game every week.

✅ Train consistently (classes aren’t optional — they’re maintenance)
✅ Get work (yes, the small jobs matter too)
✅ Create work (short films, monologues, scenes, content)
✅ Volunteer for formal shorts/student films and build real credits
✅ Stay sharp with peripheral acting jobs:

🎭 Role play / corporate training
🎙 Voiceover
🩺 Medical role play (nurse/patient scenarios)
🕵️ Mystery events
📣 Promo & immersive experiences

Some actors look down on this stuff…

But the real pros know.

👇 Join the movement here:

message.text:
STOP WAITING. START ACTING. 🎬

If you’re an actor… you need to be constantly acting.

Not “thinking about acting.”
Not “planning to act next year.”
Not waiting for someone to pick you.

Because the actors who win?
They don’t wait for permission.

They stay in the game every week.

✅ Train consistently (classes aren’t optional — they’re maintenance)
✅ Get work (yes, the small jobs matter too)
✅ Create work (short films, monologues, scenes, content)
✅ Volunteer for formal shorts/student films and build real credits
✅ Stay sharp with peripheral acting jobs:

🎭 Role play / corporate training
🎙 Voiceover
🩺 Medical role play (nurse/patient scenarios)
🕵️ Mystery events
📣 Promo & immersive experiences

Some actors look down on this stuff…

But the real pros know.

👇 Join the movement here:
linktr.ee/mattzina

items.text:
Hello all,

I’m a filmmaker from Markham, Ontario directing a feature film funded by Telefelim Canada’s Talent-To-Watch program. Searching for my  TWO leads, both of Filipino background. If you think you know anyone that would be interested please share.

Info below!

CANADA-WIDE CASTING CALL (Non-Union) // AWAY WITH DAD // FEATURE FILM

Paid Opportunity
Filming Location: Renfrew County, Ontario
Tentative dates: Mid August - End of September 2026

Set in Algonquin Park, Away With Dad is a candid story of a father and his adult son who make the drastic decision of going on a backpacking trip in the wilderness with no running water or electricty in order to focus on creating a stronger bond between them.

Casting for the following Lead Roles:
Thomas - Male, Filipino, 45 - 65 years old, speaks Visayan or Tagalog
TJ - Male, Filipino, 20 - 35 years old

NO ACTING EXPERIENCE REQUIRED. Camping experience an asset. Must be a Canadian Citizen. 

Director: Kyle Credo Producer: Farah Abdo 
If interested please email office@awdfilm.com a photo of yourself and a video (2 minutes MAX) stating your full name, what languages you can speak. For the remainder of the video please tell us about yourself: your upbringing, where you grew up and your hobbies, likes, dislikes, etc. Anything that helps us get to know you better!"

items.text:
**CASTING CALL — FEATURE FILM — VANCOUVER**

**PAID BUT FORGOTTEN**
Independent Psychological Thriller / Drama

Casting principal roles for an upcoming feature film currently in development.

**PROJECT**

A once-celebrated writer living in isolation becomes convinced his life is being shaped by forces beyond his control. As coincidences and fractured memories collapse past and present into a single unsettling design, others are drawn into a story that may be writing them too.

**Visual tone:** Modern black-and-white cinematography with selective color accents.
Character-driven, cinematic, psychologically grounded.

**ROLES**

**RHONDA**
Female, 35–50
Black actors strongly encouraged to submit. Trans women welcome.
A high-profile investigative journalist — sharp, charismatic, relentless — whose professional curiosity becomes personal entanglement.

**Feature shoot:** approx. 1–2 days

**LEROY**
Male, 35–50
Indigenous / First Nations actors strongly encouraged to submit.
A community leader rebuilding his life while helping others do the same — grounded, soulful, quietly powerful.

**Feature shoot:** approx. 3 days

**PREVIEW SHOOT (Proof-of-Concept)**

Actors cast will carry forward into the feature.

A short **non-union, unpaid preview shoot** will capture approximately **15 seconds of finished footage per role** for a **45-second funding trailer** supporting post-production grant applications.

**Preview shoot timeframe:** ASAP – January to early February 2026
**Time commitment:** approx. 1–2 hours per actor

**FEATURE PRODUCTION**

**Principal photography:** February 2026 — Vancouver
**Feature compensation:** $225/day for principal roles

Shooting days scheduled efficiently and flexibly to accommodate availability.

**AUDITION PROCESS**

Selected actors will receive sides and a self-tape request.
Shortlisted performers may be invited for a brief virtual or in-person callback.
Grounded, natural performances preferred.

**SUBMISSIONS**

Please send:

• Headshot
• Resume
• Demo reel or performance link (if available)

**Submit to:** casting@horstcreative.ca
**Submission deadline:** January 23, 2026

Writer / Director: Jared Horst
Production: Horst Creative
horstcreative.ca

items.text:
We’re looking to fill a few remaining crew positions for an upcoming 48 Hour Film Challenge short, shooting at a house in San Pedro.
We have a name talent cast and experienced crew. Shooting a spooky love story.

Still seeking:
    •    1st AC
    •    Grip
    •    1st AD
    •    Sound Mixer
    •    2 Production Assistants
Details:
    •    Shooting on ARRI and RED
    •    Fast-paced, fun 48-hour challenge environment
    •    Copy, credit, and meals provided
    •    Small, stellar team that values professionalism and good energy
This is a great chance to collaborate, meet new people, and create something strong under pressure. If you thrive in a quick-turn creative setting and want to be part of a solid team, we’d love to connect! DM or email benjaminrvigil@gmail.com (cc: Kennedy@kennedymartin.com) with your role, experience, and availability.

LOOKING FOR A COMPOSER

Hi everyone! I’m looking for a **composer** for a 8 **-minute student short film** called *Space Baby*.

A **sci-fi Comedy / 80s-inspired film** about two college students who find a baby alien and end up raising it as their kid.

The film is already shot, and I’m looking for someone to create an **80s sci-fi themed score**, mainly for emotional and atmospheric moments. Think inspiration like **Back to the Future, Ghostbusters, and The Breakfast Club** (synthy, warm, nostalgic vibes).

This is a **paid opportunity**.

If you’re interested, please  email at wagnercarrera138@gmail. com me with samples of your work. Thanks!

items.text:
PAID: Looking for a production assistant for documentary.
Hi everyone! My name is Bryanna Reynolds and I am an independent filmmaker based here in Los Angeles but originally from Australia. I am producing my first short film "The Last Eight" and I am looking for a production assistant.

The documentary tells the story of the city of Burbank Community coming together over the course of 2025 and building a float for the 137th Rose Parade in Pasadena, California. 

The float is a pirate ship and the overall film has a sense of adventure, urgency and emotional reflection of people coming together. 

I need a production assistant to help me with festival research, submission, and general outreach to communities and people involved in the float. The job can be remote. 

Thank you so much! I look forward to connecting with you all! 

Please reach out on the official page The Last Eight or on Instagram @thelasteight_film

Baśka Modra, Młoda (27) – bardzo wysportowana trenerka personalna, ładna, nieco zadziorna
Data: 22.01

Proszę o zgłoszenia tylko mailowe, tylko od osób które jeszcze nie grały w 20. sezonie „Gliniarzy” (od września 2025)

4. Aktualne zdjęcie
5. Krótki opis doświadczenia

Nowy Rok – nowe postanowienia i nowe brzmienia!
Zespół wokalny ogłasza nabór głosów żeńskich i męskich. Jeśli chcesz wreszcie zrobić coś dla siebie, wrócić do śpiewu albo rozpocząć nową muzyczną przygodę – to idealny moment.
Próby odbywają się w każdą sobotę o godz. 10.00
w budynku Sokoła przy ul. Kościuszki w Niepołomicach.
Spełnij noworoczne postanowienie i dołącz do zespołu, w którym muzyka łączy ludzi i daje radość. 🎶

WARSZAWA!!!   PILNE!!!   GLINIARZE!!!
Do najnowszego odcinka serialu „Gliniarze”, realizowanego w Warszawie (i bliskich okolicach) poszukuję kobiety do następujących roli:

Baśka Modra, Młoda (27) – bardzo wysportowana trenerka personalna, ładna, nieco zadziorna

Data: 22.01

Stawka: 250 zł netto

Proszę o zgłoszenia tylko mailowe, tylko od osób które jeszcze nie grały w 20. sezonie „Gliniarzy” (od września 2025)

Chętne Panie zapraszam do wysyłania zgłoszeń na adres: casting.outset@interia.pl

W tytule maila proszę o wpisanie nazwy postaci.

W treści maila proszę o zawarcie następujących informacji:

1. Wiek/wzrost/waga

2. Nr tel. Do kontaktu

3. Linki do sowich materiałów video – demo/wizytówka/scenki castingowe

4. Aktualne zdjęcie

5. Krótki opis doświadczenia

Nie zwracamy kosztów dojazdu/noclegu

*DIGITAL ART OPEN-CALL OPPORTUNITY IN NYC*

Start the new year by exhibiting your work **on Madison Ave** in NYC. This one-night digital art show at a five-level speakeasy art studio inside Herbwell, seeks artworks exploring **rebirth, evolution, endings, beginnings, and transformation**. Showcase your art in the same neighborhood as monumental museums and galleries like the MoMa.

All digital mediums welcome: Digital Paintings & Illustration, 3D Modeling & Digital Sculpture, Digital Collage & Vector Art, Digital Photography, Pixel Art, GIF Art / Animation, Glitch Art, Generative Art, Augmented Reality (AR) Art, Virtual Reality (VR) Art, AI Art, Mixed Media (with digital components), Video Art & Motion Graphics, NFTs & Blockchain-Backed Works, Interactive & Installation-Based Digital Works, Derivative works (where you hold rights to exhibit), Scanned Physical Works

**Why submit?**

• Showcase your work in one of NYC’s most prestigious art corridors
• Photos, documentation, and press coverage included
• Connect with curators, collectors, and international artists
• Feature in a multi-disciplinary event blending digital art, traditional art, and live music

If your work speaks to stepping into something new — we’d love to see it.

**Apply here:** [https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC](https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC)

items.text:
Hi!

Last year, my co-director and I reached out to cast for a short film. Unfortunately, we had to postpone casting and push filming to early 2026. If you submitted your tape last year and are still interested, please send in a new one. This will help us determine your availability for the new dates.

We are excited to share that we’re ready now to restart pre-production on the passion project that we’ve been writing and working on for the last year and a half.

Below, you’ll find all the necessary information and three different casting opportunities.

**Project Overview**

**Project Title:** Token

**Genre:** Psychological Thriller

**Logline:** Ai, a young aspiring chef, is given the opportunity of a lifetime. A chance to work for one of the wealthiest inventors in the world. Upon meeting him, however, things take an unexpected turn as an introductory dinner becomes a test for his most recent invention.

**Production Type:** Non-union (passion project).

**Key Logistics**

**Production Dates:** February 28th to March 1st, 2026.

**Hours:** Two 12-hour days for Ai and Kenzo. One 12-hour day for Emma.

**Location:** TBD. In or near Denver, CO.

**Compensation:** Ai and Kenzo will get a flat fee of $100 for the two days (not $100 per day). Emma will get $50 for the one day.

**Rehearsal:** Will happen online. Date TBD.

**Meals:** Lunch provided.

**Travel/Lodging:** Not providing transportation. **Local hire only**.

**Submission Requirements**

**How To Submit:** Fill out this form:[ [[https://token.fillout.com/t/6BxYpt1JsNus](https://token.fillout.com/t/6BxYpt1JsNus)](https://token.fillout.com/t/6BxYpt1JsNus)](https://token.fillout.com/t/6BxYpt1JsNus)

**Instructions:** The form and email you’ll receive will guide you through the steps of downloading sides and submitting your tape.

**Audition Material:** We are asking for a self-tape.

**Deadline:** January 25th, 2026 submissions close.

**Roles and Character Breakdowns**

**AI (20’s)** - Reserved yet determined aspiring chef who has devoted her life to mastering culinary arts. While she possesses the drive and ambition to succeed in the competitive world of professional cooking, her family-oriented nature means she’ll never sacrifice the people she loves for personal achievement. She forms deep emotional bonds quickly and genuinely, wearing her heart on her sleeve when it comes to those she cares about.

**KENZO (40’s – 50’s)** – An influential inventor who operates with an iron grip on both his work and those around him. Deeply rooted in tradition yet obsessed with perfection, he is currently consumed by his latest creation and will stop at nothing to see it realized exactly as he envisions. He is a man who firmly believes the ends justifies the means as morality takes a backseat to achievement. He has no qualms about making difficult, even ruthless decisions if they serve his ultimate purpose. His need for control extends beyond his invention into every aspect of his life, making him potentially dangerous when his goals are threatened. He carries himself with the authority of someone who has earned his influence and expects others to fall in line.

**EMMA (30’s)** – A firm and exacting woman who serves as Kenzo’s right-hand in maintaining the estate. She runs operations with militant efficiency, holding everyone under her authority to impossibly high standards while tolerating no excuses or shortcuts. Her entire existence revolves around a singular, almost obsessive goal; earning and maintaining Kenzo’s approval. This focus causes her to see the world in black and white, where results are all that matter and personal considerations are irrelevant distractions. Her unwavering loyalty to Kenzo and his vision drives every decision she makes as she expects the same level of dedication from everyone else, creating an atmosphere of pressure and control wherever she goes.

**Other**

*As a word of warning, we do make reference to suicide.

You can go to our website to learn more about us and the film. Link: [[[https://tylerfreemanfilms.com](https://tylerfreemanfilms.com)](https://tylerfreemanfilms.com/)](https://tylerfreemanfilms.com/)

Any questions, please email tyler@tylerfreemanfilms.com.

items.text:
**🎬 CASTING CALL: *****Illusions of Grandeur ***

******Live Action******

*A Short Film by *Jordan Jackson

**Genre: Drama / Coming-of-Age**

**Tone: Gritty realism with a child’s imaginative lens**

**COMPENSATION: Unpaid :( , Lunch, Copy of Footage **

**Filming Dates: End of January or Early February **

***Please Submit by January 20th, 2025 :)**

**[EMAIL jjacks24@uccs.edu FOR SIDES]**

**LOCATION: Colorado Springs **

**Logline:**

A young boy’s love for his superhero idol blurs with reality when he discovers his hero — and his father — isn’t the savior he imagined.

**🧢 JOEY (6–12)**
**Description:** Innocent, imaginative, and full of heart. Joey escapes his unstable home through superhero fantasies. He believes good always wins — even when the world around him says otherwise.
**Type:** Young actor capable of conveying wonder, playfulness, and heartbreak.

**🌹 ELISE (16–20)**
**Description:** Joey’s older sister and reluctant guardian. She’s grown up too fast — sharp, tired, protective. She carries both resentment and love for her family’s situation.
**Tone:** Grounded realism, emotional restraint with underlying warmth.

**🕯️ JOEY’S MOM (Late 20s–30s)**
**Description:** Overworked and emotionally exhausted. Trying to hold her family together while fighting her own quiet collapse. Her phone calls reveal more than she ever tells her children.
**Type:** Actor who can express fatigue, vulnerability, and quiet strength.

**🥀 GENTLEMAN PERFECT / JAMES (30s–40s)**
**Description:** Once a man of pride and potential — now homeless, addicted, and haunted by his past. In Joey’s eyes, he’s a superhero; in reality, he’s a fallen one. A tragic, layered role requiring depth, subtlety, and broken charisma.
**Tone:** Complex mix of dignity, shame, and fading hope.

**🗝️ HOMELESS MAN (40s–50s)**
**Description:** A street survivor who represents the darker side of desperation. Not evil, but lost. Brief appearance, but a pivotal moment showing Joey’s innocence colliding with danger.

**💔 YOUNG MAN / MUGGER (18–22)**
**Description:** A mirror of what Joey could become — young, broke, trying to survive. His confrontation with Gentleman Perfect reveals both the world’s cruelty and the man’s lingering morality.

**💄 WOMAN (20s–30s)**
**Description:** Victim of the mugging; small role but emotionally grounding. Her scene reinforces Joey’s belief that Gentleman Perfect is still a hero — just before that belief unravels.

**👬 ERIC (18–22)**
**Description:** Joey’s friend ten years later. Provides contrast and realism — he wasn’t there to see the “heroics.” Grounded, observant, a reminder that nostalgia and truth rarely match.

**🌇 OLDER JOEY (Late teens–20s)**
**Description:** Once full of imagination, now hardened by betrayal. Still searching for something heroic in a world that let him down. His closing narration brings the story full circle.

**📅 Production Notes**
* **Setting:** Urban neighborhood; mostly night exteriors.
* **Tone:** Visual realism with moments of childhood wonder.
* **Themes:** Hero worship, family, addiction, disillusionment, legacy.
* **Shooting Length:** 10–12 pages (~10–15 minutes).

******Live Action******

*A Short Film by *Jordan Jackson

**Genre: Drama / Coming-of-Age**

**Tone: Gritty realism with a child’s imaginative lens**

Nürnberg! Wir laden euch zum Networking-Treffen am 12.01. ein! Offen für alle (semi)professionellen Schauspieler, Filmemacher oder Creative aus der Branche, die sich vernetzen möchten und 2026 gemeinsam Projekte umsetzen möchten :)
Unser Acting Circle war ursprünglich für Schauspieler gedacht, die gemeinsam proben, Schauspieltechniken erarbeiten oder sich über das Business austauschen wollten! 2026 möchte wir aktiver in das Filmen und Produzieren gehen, einige unserer Teilnehmer schreiben bereits an ersten Skripten! 

Die Idee ist auch, etwa 1x/Monat ein Treffen auf die Beine zu stellen, an dem wir üben - hier sind natürlich auch Filmemacher oder Regiebegeisterte eingeladen, die sich auf der anderen Seite der Kamera ausprobieren möchten! 

Das Treffen soll dazu dienen, sich unverbindlich kennenzulernen! Da unsere Räumlichkeiten nur begrenzt Platz bieten, ist eine Teilnahme nur mit vorheriger Anmeldung möglich! Schick uns über Instagram ein paar Infos zu dir und deinen bisherigen Erfahrungen zu!

Instagram.com/actingcircle 

Wir freuen uns auf deine Nachricht!

Actors!. Unleash your creativity and join a vibrant community of passionate filmmakers who are dedicated to bringing stories to life! Together, we'll craft captivating narrative films, forge valuable connections, and fuel our artistic visions. 

This is more than just filmmaking; it's a journey to elevate our craft and careers to new heights! Every Saturday from 4-6 PM near DTLA, we gather to share ideas, collaborate, and inspire one another. If you're truly committed to making an impact in the world of film and ready to embark on this exciting adventure, we invite you to become a part of our filmmaking family. Membership is completely free! 

Complete this form to join us. [https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7](https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExOWgxMkV1M0hERHZPcnRiZHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR5k9IvyEVLNR7KSIH-49als_mHzt2jmGaMVG-0US9AEEf0j7Noco2gsk8uinQ_aem_Bhp-OAZ6lp-AUQSLYq-m5Q)

Hi all, hope this is okay to post here. I’ve created a new tool for actors that allows them to keep a track of all our their previous castings/meetings and manage their relationships with casting directors, directors and producers. It is meant as a calm and intuitive space that allows you to view and get instant insights into your career.

It is called CueLine

cueline.co.uk

Check it out, would love feedback on it if anybody does give it a go.

**SØGER BØRN (7–11 ÅR) TIL FILMSCENE I ØGADERNE I AARHUS I WEEKENDEN (D. 10. eller 11. januar)**

Vi søger en lille gruppe børn (7–11 år) til en sjov filmscene i Øgaderne **lørdag eller søndag kl. 9–12** (det tidspunkt der passer jer bedst).

Børnene skal lave uskyldige nytårsløjer med barberskum og knaldperler. Der er ingen replikker og ingen skuespilerfaring er nødvendig.

Der er varm kakao til børnene og kaffe til de voksne 

Vi er et filmhold fra filmskolen DOKTRIN i Aarhus og optager vores afgangsfilm, som får premiere i efteråret 2026. I er selvfølgelig inviteret til premieren<3

Vil i være med?

Skriv en privat besked, mail til **laurits.helligsoe@gmail.com** eller ring på **23909944**.

🎤 NATIONWIDE CASTING CALL – SINGERS WANTED 🎤
We are seeking strong vocalists and musical-theatre-style performers for well-paid solo and duo Care Home touring work launching throughout 2026.

Auditions will take place in February, and we’re inviting performers from all regions of the UK to apply.

Audition hubs:

 • SW London (for all London-based)

 • Bristol (South West)

 • Birmingham (Midlands)

 • Leeds (North East)

 • Manchester (North West)

With multiple new shows in a variety of styles launching across 2026, this is an exciting opportunity for reliable, engaging performers who love connecting with audiences.

📩 To apply:

Please email auditionsuk2025@gmail.com with:

 • A brief introduction about yourself

 • Your showreel or a rough vocals video

🚗 Driving licence essential

items.text:
🎭 CASTING OUVERT
JOB – LA COMÉDIE MUSICALE

Création originale – Œuvre déposée à la SACD

⸻

🔥 LE PROJET

Inspirée du Livre de Job, cette comédie musicale originale raconte l’épreuve d’un homme juste confronté à la perte, au jugement et au silence de Dieu.

Un spectacle intense, incarné, vocalement exigeant, où la voix est au cœur du drame.

⸻

🎤 PROFILS RECHERCHÉS

🔹 CHANTEURS / CHANTEUSES

 • Excellente technique vocale

 • Forte présence scénique

 • Capacité à porter une émotion profonde

 • À l’aise avec une écriture dramatique et spirituelle

Tous âges – Tous profils bienvenus

⸻

🎭 RÔLES PRINCIPAUX

 • JOB – voix masculine puissante (ténor ou baryton clair), grande intensité émotionnelle

 • SATAN (L’ADVERSAIRE) – présence charismatique, voix sombre

 • LA FEMME DE JOB – voix forte, expressive

 • ÉLIFAZ / BILDAD / SOFAR – voix affirmées, personnages de confrontation

 • ENSEMBLE / CHŒUR

⸻

🎶 UNIVERS MUSICAL

 • Pop symphonique

 • Ballades dramatiques

 • Chœurs bibliques

 • Influences latines élégantes

⸻

📍 INFORMATIONS

 • Lieu : Paris

 • Auditions : sur sélection

 • Répétitions : calendrier en cours

 • Statut : création originale

⸻

📩 CANDIDATURE

Envoyer :

 • CV artistique

 • Photo

 • Lien audio ou vidéo (chant)

👉 casting@job-lacomedie-musicale.com

⸻

✨

« Nu je suis sorti du ventre de ma mère,

nu j’y retournerai. »

JOB – La Comédie Musicale

🌐 job-lacomedie-musicale.com

sharedPost.text:
Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 3/2026

NEUES KOOPERATIONSKINO UND NEUER SENDEPARTNER

Ab dieser Ausgabe präsentiert nun auch das Campus und City Radio St Pölten (jeweils Dienstag 18 - 19h) unsere Movietime. Und passend dazu gibt es mit dem Cinema Paradiso in der Landeshauptstadt ein weiteres Kino, von dem wir Highlights vorstellen. 

In Sachen neuen Filmen starten mit EXTRAWURST und THE HOUSEMAID zwei Streifen, die nicht unterschiedlicher sein können.

Im Ruhestand ausruhen? Nicht so bei unserem Interviewgast Sabine Wolfinger. Seit sie in Pension ist, gibt sie ordentlich Gas, egal ob als Komparsin oder beim Heilfasten.
 
Musikalisch gedenken wir in unserer Sendung an die kürzlich verstorbene Brigitte Bardot. 

Mittwoch 14.1.2026 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon

**Odense: Legesyge børnefamilier søges til fotoshoot! Gerne internationale.**

**** English below***** *****

**Calling all parents to children aged 6-12 **who would like to spend a couple of hours playing with us at a cozy photo/video shoot focused on digital family activities related to LEGO.

No acting required, just a relaxed family session and fun activities in a home-like setting, facilitated by Stupid Studio.

Everyone is welcome to apply. Just bring your best energy and inner child! We provide a gift card for a fun day at a theme/activity park or experience attraction as a thank you for participating.

**Date:** Saturday, January 24, 2026 (sooon 😉)
**Duration: **Approx. 2 hours, between 9:00 AM and 4:00 PM
**Location: **In or around Odense
**What: **Photo and video (no sound) of digital play and shared screen time

Interested? Send an email to **jonas@stupid-studio.com** with names, ages, and a very short introduction to your family (3–5 people), and maybe a selfie, - and we’ll get back to you as soon as possible.

items.text:
Altarena Playhouse (Alameda, CA) is holding auditions for *‘Night Mother *by Marsha Norman, Directed by ShawnJ West

 

Performance Dates: May 29th through June 28th     

(Fridays/Saturdays at 7:30 pm, and Sundays at 2:00 pm)

 

SHOW SYNOPSIS:

Thelma Cates is a mother and widow who lives with her daughter, Jessie. Jessie is the divorced mother of a troubled son who struggles with life as an unemployed epileptic. She confesses to her mother that she is going to take her life. Tonight. As Mama pleads with her to reconsider her decision, old secrets are revealed, and long-ignored feelings rise to the surface. The mother-daughter bond between Jessie and Mama becomes stronger and lovelier than ever, making it possible for Jessie to end her noisy, cluttered existence, and take a quieter, calmer path with closure and love.

 

AUDITION DATES:

Monday, January 19th at 7:00pm and Saturday, January 24th at 1:00pm, by appointment

 

Callbacks: Monday, February 2nd, 7-10 pm, by invitation

 

Rehearsals begin April 25, 2026 at 11:00 am

 

Auditions will be held at the Altarena Playhouse, 1409 High Street, Alameda

 

Performers of all races and ethnicities are encouraged to audition.

 

Non-AEA only. $500 Reimbursement for expenses

 

 

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

THELMA “MAMA” CATES (Female, 60s)

Warm, talkative, and steeped in the routines of her home life, Thelma is a woman who uses chatter, caretaking, and small comforts to keep the world steady. Beneath her practical exterior, she carries deep anxieties, regrets, and unspoken guilt that surface as the night unfolds. Actors should bring emotional dexterity, humor grounded in truth, and the ability to navigate sharp tonal shifts as Mama confronts an unthinkable situation with both denial and fierce love.

 

JESSIE CATES (Female, 40s)

Direct, methodical, and emotionally contained, Jessie is a woman who has lived with chronic illness, disappointment, and a profound sense of futility. She speaks plainly and acts with quiet determination, revealing a grounded pragmatism rather than melodrama. Actors should bring a nuanced stillness, clarity of intention, and the ability to reveal the powerful internal life beneath Jessie’s calm, steady presence.

 

To sign up and for audition sides, visit:  [https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night](https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night)

 

Please contact Katina at [artisticdirector@altarena.org](mailto:artisticdirector@altarena.org) should you have any questions.

Hi Everyone!

I'm excited to share that the new casting platform, Castingly, is almost at **600 members!** As we prepare to meet with casting directors to showcase the site, I'm actively seeking actors interested in being featured as "example profiles." If you’d like to participate, please comment below and let me know!

To effectively show off all the site's capabilities, we need users to complete **100% of their profiles.** 

If you're not interested in being showcased but still want to explore the site, you can check us out at [www.castingly.com](http://www.castingly.com/). 

**Membership is free through 2026!** We'll also be rolling out casting breakdowns within the next few weeks. Feel free to reach out if you have any questions!

**TITLE:** Hoodwink

**LOCATION:** Los Angeles, CA, USA (TBC)

**PRODUCTION DATE:** 30 January – 1 February 2026

**PAID, UNPAID OR PROFIT SHARE:** Pay TBC (Non-Union)

**HOW TO APPLY:** Visit [https://actorsandextras.com/casting-calls](https://actorsandextras.com/casting-calls) for casting details.

---

🎬 **CASTING CALL – “HOODWINK” (LEAD ROLES / AUDITION REQUIRED)**

A dramatic project seeking strong, emotionally layered performers. **Real couples are encouraged to audition.**

---

### **ROLES AVAILABLE**

**Kwame – Lead**

Male, late 20s–early 30s | Black / African American or Ambiguous / Multi-Racial

Height: **5’10”+**

A man obsessed with creating the “perfect” life and marriage. Beneath the surface, inner turmoil and betrayal fuel a vindictive mindset as he seeks revenge on his unfaithful wife.

**Alana – Lead**

Female, late 20s–early 30s | Black / African American or Ambiguous / Multi-Racial

Height: **5’5”–5’9”**

Passionate yet suspicious. Once devoted to her marriage, Alana now seeks comfort elsewhere.

---

### **IMPORTANT NOTE**

This script contains **partial nudity, passionate kissing/intimate scenes, and violence**.

A **qualified Intimacy Coordinator** will be on set, and a **small, closed crew** will be used during intimate scenes to ensure professionalism and care.

---

📍 **Location:** Los Angeles area (exact location TBC)

🎥 **Type:** Film

🎬 **Union Status:** Non-Union

📅 **Shoot Dates:** Jan 30 – Feb 1, 2026

---

📩 **HOW TO APPLY**

Apply via Actors and Extras as a Talent PRO member with a **1-month FREE trial:**

➡️ [https://actorsandextras.com/casting-calls](https://actorsandextras.com/casting-calls)

**Castings for you, delivered straight to your inbox.**

👉 [https://www.actorsandextras.com](https://www.actorsandextras.com)

Know someone perfect for this? Please share this casting with them.

---

🔍 *This casting has been shared by Actors and Extras as a service to our talent directory members. We have received permission to share it and believe it to be legitimate. However, we strongly encourage all applicants to exercise due diligence and independently verify the details of the project before proceeding.*

Hello everyone,
We are a young French filmmaking team currently developing an ambitious project that will be shot across three countries: France, England and Morocco (planned for spring/summer 2026).
This is a very personal, carefully written story with a strong festival ambition (Clermont-Ferrand, Côté Court, Premiers Plans, international festivals, etc.).
Visually driven, intimate, cinematic atmosphere.
We are looking for:
Actors and actresses aged 18–25 (very open regarding look, style, background)
All profiles welcome: complete beginners with strong motivation, drama school students, emerging actors, faces already seen in shorts, etc.
Important info:
•  Unpaid project (very low/no budget – young indie cinema)
•  But real opportunity: meaningful role(s), several weeks of shooting, travel (France/UK/Morocco), serious festival run potential, nice team, high-quality visuals
How to apply (mandatory elements):
Send an email to:
rivierebouchaud@gmail.com
Required in your email:
•  Recent photos (portrait + at least one medium/full-body shot if possible)
•  A few words about yourself / your background / why this project interests you
(Optional but appreciated: showreel link / theatre recording / self-tape)
Please put in the subject line:
CASTING – [Your first name] – [your city/country]
We recommend sending your application within the next 3 weeks so we can move forward smoothly with selections.
Thank you so much for your time and energy!
We’re really excited to discover new faces to bring this international adventure to life.
Looking forward to reading you

AUDITIONS OPEN: Collection of Short Plays in March in London

Happy New Year! We’re Broadmai Productions, and we’re excited to announce that auditions are now open for our upcoming performance, HAYWIRE: The Dark Side of New Technology. The performances will be held at The Drayton Arms on 22nd & 23rd March 2026, starting at 7:30 PM each night. (Cast required all day on 22nd March for get-in and from 18:00 each night). 

Auditions will be online and open tomorrow, 13th January, and continue until 24th January. All ages, genders and levels of experience welcome. If you’re interested in auditioning, please email us at: contact@broadmai-productions.co.uk

Please express interest by 23rd January.

Once you reach out, we’ll send you the scripts for the four short plays: PostMax6000, Wonderful, Beyond the Grave, and Simon. 

_______

AUDITION DETAILS:

 • Auditions are 20-minute slots. You will be asked to audition with 2-3 pages of your choice from the provided scripts.

 • Ideally, be off book, but it’s fine if not. 

 • The characters are flexible in terms of gender and age, except those for Beyond the Grave, which requires two male actors who resemble father and son.

_______

PLAY DESCRIPTIONS:

 • PostMax 6000: The PostMax 6000 is invented! A vast underground postal system capable of delivering

hundreds of letters across the country per second! But what’s this?! It’s just sucked Kinkelbert George inside! Will he be delivered to freedom? Or lost in postal purgatory?

 • Wonderful: Ben signs up for a research programme for a new-age medical device. It can detect hereditary

illness and diseases that he could develop…but it also lets him know, and hear, exactly how his

ancestors died. As detections become increasingly intense, Ben learns that knowledge about death is better left untold — especially when it comes to children.

 • Beyond the Grave: A mysterious phone is delivered. When it rings, Reece answers it and finds his deceased father on the other end. Overwhelmed to hear his voice again and to learn that there is a way to bring him back to life, Reece starts to wonder if the rules of death are better left unbroken…

 • Simon: Simon has an all-inclusive getaway booked and paid for by his work. The location is perfect, the

hotel is perfect, Simon is perfect. And so is Simon — the other Simon. And the other Simon. Wait, how many Simons are there?! Who’s the real Simon?!

_______

REHEARSALS: 

 • Rehearsals will be in-person in London, with a commitment of 1-2 sessions per week until the performances.

_______

COMPENSATION:

 • This will be a profit-share arrangement, with profits distributed after expenses are covered.

Edited

🎬 CASTING CALL – HORROR feature film 🎬
Hey everyone,
I’m currently looking for actors for an independent horror project titled:
FLYING TO MADNESS
This is a psychological horror film inspired by travel vlogs, haunted locations, and reality-bending horror. With a lot of twists
👻 ABOUT THE PROJECT
3 sisters travel to Ibiza for a girls holiday.
After taking drugs and exploring a remote location, they become trapped in a looping nightmare involving a haunted house that won’t let them leave.
Think:
Psychological horror
Creeping dread rather than cheap jump scares
This is a low-budget indie project, made for experience, showreels, and festival submissions.
🎭 ROLES AVAILABLE

ACTRESS 1
Female, early–mid 20s
Slim built or curvy 
Confident, outgoing, “leader” type
Comfortable acting on camera and improvising dialogue
Lots of screen time available 

ACTRESS 2
Female, early–mid 20s
Slim built or curvy
More cautious / sarcastic personality
Strong reactions and emotional range
Lots of screen time available 

ACTRESS 3 
Female early - mid 20s
Slim built
Shy/Inclosed soft voice
Good with emotional expressions
Lots of screen time available 

ACTOR 4
Male, any age 20s–40s about 6 foot plus. 
Slim built
Mysterious, unsettling presence
Minimal dialogue but strong physical acting
Horror-focused role
No previous acting experience required — just commitment and reliability.

📍 LOCATION
Filming location: (UK-based project)
Scotland four days in September 
Southend beach for one hour any time available 
Hotel scenes is for half a day but can do during scotland trip
London basement for two hours in October 
Nightclub scene for two hours in April the 22nd at 6pm as location I’d already booked
And an hour at a studio for greenscreen Footage. Anytime available 
Passport might be needed for actor 1 and 2 as we need a scene on a plane or might be able to edit in with greenscreen effect
Mostly interior scenes
Small cast, long shoot schedule
💰 PAYMENT
No payment at the time of filming but
10% rotary payments after the film sells. In the cinemas and app stores. Small indi project
but travel expenses covered as can be picked up by the director from your location you want. And taking to the filming location. And Brought home after the scenes
If your making your own way to the scenes we can’t cover travelling 
Food provided on shoot days
Full credit given
Will help to spice up your portfolio and get more experience as main actors in the film.
📩 HOW TO APPLY
If interested, please message our private company WhatsApp on 07492853834 
Or if you want you can email on mpl.87@outlook.com 

with:
Your name
Age
Any acting experience (if any)
A recent photo or selfie
Availability
also send a short intro video.
If you love horror, indie films, or want experience working on a creative project, I’d love to hear from you.
Thanks!
— Matt Littlechild 
Writer / Director – Flying to Madness

topComments.text: Do you really believe your ultra low budget film will have cinema distribution?

This is an abysmal casting call. A feature length unpaid is already a bad start. But you won't even cover expenses if they need to travel unless you can directly pick them up? I'd be shocked if more than 15 people submit to this.

There's no incentive to do it. The idea is generic - so from an artistic viewpoint, there's not much to gain. There's no pay, which is understandable at the indie level - but I've never seen somebody not offer to pay transport. Ever in my life.

And why would you book filming dates before you cast? Why do people keep doing this?

I'm not being harsh. I've just ran a very successful casting campaign for my fourth short film. This is awful. I don't see why any actor would take it other than very low calibre, bad actors who are desperate..

Paying transport and food is a minimum.

**Freelance Performers Wanted – Join the Pink Pixie Parties Team!**

We’re growing fast and expanding into **London and surrounding areas**, alongside our regular regions in **Yorkshire, Nottinghamshire & Lincolnshire**.
If you’re **based south of Leeds**, or within easy reach of **Northampton the Midlands or London**, please do get in touch — we’d love to hear from you!

We’re looking for bright, confident **performers** to join our incredible team! If you’re reliable, full of energy, and love working with children, you’ll fit right in. Our roles include performing as **Princesses, Popstars and more** at birthday parties and corporate events.

**Pay:**
* 1 hour – **£75 **plus travel door to door
* 2 hours – **£95 **plus travel door to door
* Travelling more than 1.5 hours? Earn **from £180 for 2 HOURS!**
*(plus mileage at 35p per mile door-to-door + £40 travel time allowance)*

We believe in paying fairly for your time, professionalism, and performance — our rates are **some of the best in the industry.**

**Why work with us:**
* Full **training provided** – no experience needed, just enthusiasm!
* A **supportive, friendly team** that truly looks after each other
* **Fun, flexible weekend work** with consistent bookings
* A company that values creativity, fairness, and professionalism

**Costumes fit UK sizes 8–10/12**
**Must drive** and have **great **weekend availability (rolling 4-month basis)

We have **immediate starts available** and **bookings coming in daily**, so don’t delay — send your details over today!

**Email only** (we won’t be checking Messenger):
b**ecky@pinkpixieparties.co.uk**

Please include:
* Your location and postcode
* Weekend availability from now until February
* Any relevant experience
* A recent photo or headshot
* Your **Instagram handle** so we can connect

Follow us:
Instagram → @theglitterpixies & @pinkpixieparties
Facebook → *The Glitter Pixies* & *Pink Pixie Parties *.

We wont be replying to FB messages directly or Comments on the post. Please email directly.

Salt & Lime Media is casting REAL COUPLES who met on the dating apps for an upcoming campaign. If this sounds like you, we’d love to hear your stories.

Adults (18+) are welcome to apply. All genders, sexualities and backgrounds are encouraged.

What we are looking for:

•⁠  ⁠Real couples who met on the dating apps

•⁠  ⁠You’re up for being on camera and sharing your story'

If this sounds like you, submit your story here for a chance to be featured in our next campaign, filming in March and will require **travel to the US**. 

Apply Here: [https://forms.gle/3JznSrqLFhAgnE5s8](https://forms.gle/3JznSrqLFhAgnE5s8)

Participants who are selected will be compensated and all travel costs covered. 

Standard background checks apply if you’re shortlisted.

Please be assured that all the information you share with us in your submission remains confidential. You can read more about our Talent Privacy Policy here: [https://saltandlimemedia.com/creator-talent-privacy-policy/](https://saltandlimemedia.com/creator-talent-privacy-policy/)

items.text:
KÜNSTLERFAMILIE - das Business-Netzwerk für Künstler:innen, Künstleragenturen und Netzwerkpartner.

KÜNSTLERFAMILIE bringt Künstler:innen miteinander und mit Partnern wie Unternehmen, Organisationen, Agenturen, Spielstätten, Ausbildungsstätten und Medien zusammen – und vereint sie in einem Business-Netzwerk.

KÜNSTLERFAMILIE-Mitglieder können sich und ihre Angebote über eigene Profile & Platzierungen präsentieren (= zusätzliche Sichtbarkeit) und sich miteinander vernetzen. 

Die Registrierung ist kostenlos - inklusive eigenem Profil und Zugang zum exklusiven Business-Netzwerk: https://kuenstlerfamilie.com/registrieren
